vincial government and venture capitalists, municipal leaders blamed Indigenous and mixed-heritage people, non-preferred immigrants, and transient labourers for local crime. Jonathan Swainger combs through police and legal records, government publications, and media commentary to demonstrate that the disorder was not so different from the rest of the province – and “respectable” white residents were often to blame. This lively account tells us about more than a particular community’s identity. It also sheds light on small-town disaffection in modern Canada.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAssassinationzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aAssassinationzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 0aCrime and racezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aCrime and racezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 0aCrimezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aCrimezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 0aCriminal lawzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aCriminal lawzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 0aGroup identityzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aGroup identityzBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 0aPolicezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aPolicezBritish ColumbiazPrince GeorgexHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Canada / Provincial, Territorial & Local / British Columbia (BC).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311127195808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP w/o University of Toronto Press 2023 eBook Packagez978311143542808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUn